textDisplay:
I know how to make a Barbie romper with a sock :)
Here are the steps:

1: cut 2 small slits on the toe of the sock (enough room for the Barbie’s arms)
2: make a slit between the 2 cuts you made in step 1. (This will be for the Barbie’s head)
3: put it on.
4: get glue, tape, sticky tack, anything sticky and stick it between the legs.
5: let dry (if needed)
6: there is nothing else to it! Do some touch ups, maybe fix some things by sticking them together, and your done!
(For step 4, I recommend using sticky tack.)
textOriginal:
I know how to make a Barbie romper with a sock :)
Here are the steps:

1: cut 2 small slits on the toe of the sock (enough room for the Barbie’s arms)
2: make a slit between the 2 cuts you made in step 1. (This will be for the Barbie’s head)
3: put it on. 
4: get glue, tape, sticky tack, anything sticky and stick it between the legs.
5: let dry (if needed)
6: there is nothing else to it! Do some touch ups, maybe fix some things by sticking them together, and your done!
(For step 4, I recommend using sticky tack.)
